{{orphan|date=November 2016}} {{italictitle}} [[File:Both Members of This Club George Bellows.jpeg|thumb|300px|''Both Members of This Club]]
'''''Both Members of This Club''''' is an [[oil painting]] by [[George Bellows]]. It hangs in the [[National Gallery of Art]] in [[Washington, D.C.|Washington DC]]. It dates to 1909 and measures {{cvt|115|x|160.5|cm|in|frac=16}}.
The Gallery writes, "''Both Members of This Club'' was inspired by the fights Bellows attended at [[Tom Sharkey|Tom Sharkey's]] Athletic Club in New York. At the time, public boxing matches were illegal in the city. Private organizations like Sharkey's made prospective fighters temporary members of the "club" on the night of the event to circumvent the law."<ref name="nga">{{cite web|title=Both Members of This Club|url=http://www.nga.gov/content/ngaweb/Collection/art-object-page.30667.html|publisher=National Gallery of Art|accessdate=30 November 2016}}</ref>
